<p>Java is <em>statically-typed</em> programming language.</p>

<p>Data types specify the different sizes and values that be stored in the variable. There are two types of data types in Java :</p>

<h3 id="java-primitive-data-types">Java Primitive Data Types</h3>

<p>There are 8 types of primitive data types  :</p>
<ul>
  <li>boolean false</li>
  <li>byte 0</li>
  <li>
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>char â€˜\u0000â€™</td>
          <td>Java uses 2 byte because it uses Unicode system instead of ASCII code system and the \u0000 is the lowest range of unicode system.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </li>
  <li>short 0</li>
  <li>int 0</li>
  <li>long 0L</li>
  <li>float 0.0f</li>
  <li>double 0.0d</li>
</ul>

